# This file is maintained by Go. DO NOT EDIT.

# The go.sum file contains the cryptographic checksums of the content of
# specific module versions. It is used by the Go module system to
# authenticate downloaded modules and ensure that the dependencies used
# in a build are exactly those recorded in the go.sum file.
#
# Each line in this file has the format:
# <module> <version>[/go.mod] <hash>
#
# - <module>: The module path (e.g., github.com/gorilla/mux).
# - <version>: The module version (e.g., v1.8.1).
# - /go.mod (optional): Indicates that the hash is for the go.